Getting Started
Prerequisites
Node.js (v14+)
Yarn (optional, but recommended)
Installation
Clone the repository:

bash
Copy code
git clone https://github.com/hassancode1/ivorytest/tree/main/frontend
Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
cd your-frontend-repo
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
yarn install
# or npm install
Rename .env.example to .env and update the variables according to your setup.

Usage
To start the development server:

bash
Copy code
yarn dev
# or npm run dev
Open your browser and go to http://127.0.0.1:5173/login to see the application.

